value:
Horda angel-cynnan, or, A compleat view of the manners, customs, arms, habits, &c. of the inhabitants of England, from the arrival of the Saxons, till the reign of Henry the Eighth
Þorða Anzel-cẏnnan
In fact in three volumes; volume 3 reads "... from the arrival of the Saxons to the present time ... In three volumes" on the title page, and bears the imprint: "Printed for Walter Shropshire, No. 158, New Bond-Street, MDCCLXXVI [1776]"; contains index for all 3 volumes, pages 1-10.
Indexes in vol. 1.
Old classmark: 474.
Binding: by Kalthoeber (ticket). Tree calf, g. rolled border; spine & board edges g.t., border g.t. on inside covers, g. lettering on red spine labels; marbled e.p. & a.e. marbled.

Þorða Anzel-cẏnnan, or, A compleat view of the manners, customs, arms, habits, &c. of the inhabitants of England, from the arrival of the Saxons, till the reign of Henry the Eighth : with a short account of the Britons, during the government of the Romans : in two volumes / by Joseph Strutt, author of the regal and ecclesiastical antiquities of England.
